==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Coistril
<hw>Cois"tril</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Prob. from OF.
<ets>coustillier</ets> groom or lad. Cf. <er>Custrel</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>An inferior groom or lad employed by an esquire to
carry the knight's arms and other necessaries.</def> <altsp>[Written
also <asp>coistrel</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A mean, paltry fellow; a coward.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Coit</ent>⟦br⟧
